jc-overlay: ephemeral tool-result attachments (keep media only for current turn)

Large PDFs/images read via the Read tool are stored as base64 attachments and
were re-sent on every request, bloating the payload until the OpenAI Responses
API rejected it (~60s, 0 tokens, bare "OpenAI Responses stream error"). This
strips tool-result media from messages older than the last user message, so the
agent still reads a PDF/image visually within the current turn, but stale media
no longer haunts the whole conversation.

Scope: tool-result attachments only (toModelOutput / assistant.tool branch).
Directly user-attached media is untouched.

--- a/packages/opencode/src/session/message-v2.ts	2026-05-27 23:21:52.864712710 -0700
+++ b/packages/opencode/src/session/message-v2.ts	2026-05-27 23:22:20.264204005 -0700
@@ -690,7 +690,19 @@
